Task: S3-T04 — Implement redirect Lambda handler
Completed: 2026-04-05

## Deliverables

### 1. cmd/redirect/main.go — Full redirect Lambda handler
- RedirectHandler struct with injected dependencies (store, cache, limiter, SQS, ipSalt)
- Full request flow: extract code → rate limit → cache check → negative cache → DynamoDB fallback → cache warm → TTL check → active check → password check → click increment → async SQS → 302 redirect
- IP hashing via SHA-256(salt + IP) per ADR-007
- Async SQS click event publishing in goroutine with 2s timeout per ADR-003
- Rate limiting before any business logic per ADR-006
- Cache-first strategy per ADR-002 with negative cache support
- UTM parameter appending to redirect URL
- Password-protected link HTML form (403 response)
- Lambda init() loads AWS config, DynamoDB, Redis, SQS, and IP salt from Secrets Manager
- All error responses as JSON with proper status codes (400, 404, 410, 429, 500)

### 2. cmd/redirect/main_test.go — 18 handler tests
- Successful redirect (302)
- Redirect with UTM params
- Rate limited (429) with headers
- Not found (404) with negative cache set
- Negative cache hit (404, no DynamoDB call)
- Expired link (410)
- Deactivated link (410)
- Click limit reached (410)
- Password-protected link shows form (403)
- Cache hit path (no DynamoDB call)
- Cache miss path (DynamoDB fallback + cache warm)
- Async SQS publish verification
- Missing code (400)
- HashIP determinism and uniqueness
- extractCode path parsing
- buildRedirectURL with/without UTM
- Store internal error (500)
- IncrementClickCount error (500)

### 3. Build & test verification
- `go mod tidy` — clean
- `go build ./...` — passes
- `go test ./cmd/redirect/... -race` — 18/18 PASS, no race conditions

